            "html": "<p>Hello fellow Gatsby-er! Welcome to part one of our community Gatsby.js tutorial.</p>\n<p>In this tutorial youâ€™ll be gently introduced to the Gatsby development environment, how to create component pages, and how to build and deploy Gatsby sites.</p>\n<p>Sit down, buckle up, and letâ€™s get going!</p>\n<h2 id=\"check-environment\"><a href=\"#check-environment\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Check Environment</h2>\n<p>Letâ€™s check first that you have everything setup to start working with Gatsby. You will need a recent version of <a href=\"nodejs.org\">Node.js</a> installed.</p>\n<p>Open a terminal window and type <code>node --version</code> then <code>npm --version</code>.</p>\n<p>You should see something like:</p>\n<p><div>\n          <a\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n            href=\"/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-e72f5.png\"\n            style=\"display: block\"\n            target=\"_blank\"\n          >\n            <div\n              class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n              style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; \"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n                style=\"padding-bottom: 74.92997198879551%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-fbfd7.png'); background-size: cover;\"\n              >\n                <img\n                  class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n                  style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #f7f0eb;\"\n                  alt=\"Check if node.js/npm is installed\"\n                  title=\"\"\n                  src=\"/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-fbfd7.png\"\n                  srcset=\"/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-bf506.png 173w,\n/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-e924d.png 345w,\n/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-fbfd7.png 690w,\n/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-89b1d.png 1035w,\n/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-9c993.png 1380w,\n/0e992af059139b1765ce926bf88efa45-e72f5.png 1428w\"\n                  sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n                />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </a>\n          </div></p>\n<p>Gatsby supports versions of Node back to v4 and NPM to v3.</p>\n<p>If you donâ€™t have Node.js installed, go to <a href=\"https://nodejs.org/\">https://nodejs.org/</a> and install the recommended version for your operating system.</p>\n<h2 id=\"creating-a-gatsby-site-from-scratch\"><a href=\"#creating-a-gatsby-site-from-scratch\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating a Gatsby site from scratch</h2>\n<p>Go to a directory on your computer for coding projects and create a new directory titled perhaps â€œmy-first-gatsby-siteâ€.</p>\n<p>Once inside the directory. Type <code>npm init</code>. This is a command to start a new Node.js project. You can just press enter through most of the questions.</p>\n<p><div>\n          <a\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n            href=\"/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-25272.png\"\n            style=\"display: block\"\n            target=\"_blank\"\n          >\n            <div\n              class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n              style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; \"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n                style=\"padding-bottom: 103.18237454100367%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-fbfd7.png'); background-size: cover;\"\n              >\n                <img\n                  class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n                  style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #f7f0eb;\"\n                  alt=\"Init new project\"\n                  title=\"\"\n                  src=\"/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-fbfd7.png\"\n                  srcset=\"/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-bf506.png 173w,\n/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-e924d.png 345w,\n/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-fbfd7.png 690w,\n/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-89b1d.png 1035w,\n/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-9c993.png 1380w,\n/762ff7f6edb194f5e0753e9787a27381-25272.png 1634w\"\n                  sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n                />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </a>\n          </div></p>\n<p>Now type <code>ls</code> to see the list of files in your folder. You should see <code>package.json</code>.</p>\n<p>Now weâ€™ll add the two dependencies required for a Gatsby siteâ€”<code>gatsby</code> and <code>gatsby-link</code>.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> --save gatsby@next gatsby-link@next</code></pre>\n<p>Installation should take a minute or two.</p>\n<p>Now type <code>cat package.json</code> and you should see that <code>gatsby</code> and <code>gatsby-link</code> are now added to the <code>package.json</code> as <code>dependencies</code>.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">~/p/my-first-gatsby-site: <span class=\"token function\">cat</span> package.json\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"name\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"my-first-gatsby-site\"</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"version\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"1.0.0\"</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"description\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"My first Gatsby site\"</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"main\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"index.js\"</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"scripts\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"test\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"echo \\\"Error: no test specified\\\" &amp;&amp; exit 1\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"author\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"\"</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"license\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"ISC\"</span>,\n  <span class=\"token string\">\"dependencies\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"^1.0.0-alpha19\"</span>,\n    <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby-link\"</span><span class=\"token keyword\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"^1.0.0-alpha16\"</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n<p>Sweet! Weâ€™re making progress ğŸ˜</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s now try running Gatsby!</p>\n<p>Gatsby has a built-in development server. Letâ€™s start it up. (TODO tell people to use the <code>gatsby-cli</code> package once thatâ€™s built).</p>\n<p>Run from your terminal <code>./node_modules/.bin/gatsby develop</code></p>\n<p>You should see shortly some text that says <code>The development server is listening at: http://localhost:8000</code>. Open that address in your browser.</p>\n<p><div>\n          <a\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n            href=\"/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-4fc8d.png\"\n            style=\"display: block\"\n            target=\"_blank\"\n          >\n            <div\n              class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n              style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; \"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n                style=\"padding-bottom: 84.07821229050279%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-fbfd7.png'); background-size: cover;\"\n              >\n                <img\n                  class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n                  style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #f7f0eb;\"\n                  alt=\"Gatsby.js development 404 page\"\n                  title=\"\"\n                  src=\"/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-fbfd7.png\"\n                  srcset=\"/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-bf506.png 173w,\n/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-e924d.png 345w,\n/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-fbfd7.png 690w,\n/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-89b1d.png 1035w,\n/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-9c993.png 1380w,\n/17407977292f6d5ada79e45c92ba811f-4fc8d.png 1432w\"\n                  sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n                />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </a>\n          </div></p>\n<p>Yeah! Itâ€™s working!!!</p>\n<p>What youâ€™re seeing is the Gatsby.js development 404 page. Letâ€™s do what it says and create a React.js component at <code>src/pages/index.js</code>.</p>\n<p>First create the <code>src/pages</code> directory.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">mkdir</span> -p src/pages</code></pre>\n<p>Then open up <code>src/pages/index.js</code> in your editor of choice and type in the â€œhello worldâ€ of components.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello world<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Save that andâ€¦ ğŸ˜®ğŸ˜®ğŸ˜®</p>\n<p><div>\n          <a\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n            href=\"/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-87989.png\"\n            style=\"display: block\"\n            target=\"_blank\"\n          >\n            <div\n              class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n              style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; \"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n                style=\"padding-bottom: 78.2874617737003%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-fbfd7.png'); background-size: cover;\"\n              >\n                <img\n                  class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n                  style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #f7f0eb;\"\n                  alt=\"It's alive!\"\n                  title=\"\"\n                  src=\"/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-fbfd7.png\"\n                  srcset=\"/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-bf506.png 173w,\n/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-e924d.png 345w,\n/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-fbfd7.png 690w,\n/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-89b1d.png 1035w,\n/6bd1448128094e82050a407402d07212-87989.png 1308w\"\n                  sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n                />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </a>\n          </div></p>\n<p>Too cool ğŸ˜</p>\n<p>Gatsbyâ€™s development server is a â€œhot reloadingâ€ server meaning any change you make to your React.js components (and later weâ€™ll learn, your data files) will hot reload in the browser.</p>\n<p>This is huge because it makes development so much faster and fun.</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s try it.</p>\n<p>Try changing â€œHello world!â€ in the component to â€œHello Gatsby!â€œ. The text in your browser should change within a second.</p>\n<p>Try some other tricks.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Gatsby letâ€™s you add â€œinline stylesâ€ via a JavaScript style â€œpropâ€ (weâ€™ll learn about other styling options later).</p>\n<p>Try making your component look like this:</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">style</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> color<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`blue`</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello Gatsby<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>   Change the color to â€œpinkâ€. Then â€œtomatoâ€.</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Add some paragraph text.</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx{5-6}\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">style</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> color<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`tomato`</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">   <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello Gatsby<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">   <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>What a world<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>Add an image</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx{7}\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">style</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> color<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`tomato`</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n   <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello Gatsby<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n   <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>What a world<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">   <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>http://lorempixel.com/400/200/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span></span>\n <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Now your screen should look something like this.</p>\n<p><div>\n          <a\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n            href=\"/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-4235e.png\"\n            style=\"display: block\"\n            target=\"_blank\"\n          >\n            <div\n              class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n              style=\"position: relative; z-index: -1; \"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n                style=\"padding-bottom: 82.23776223776224%;position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-fbfd7.png'); background-size: cover;\"\n              >\n                <img\n                  class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n                  style=\"width: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px #f7f0eb;\"\n                  alt=\"Screen Shot 2017-06-03 at 11.57.10 AM\"\n                  title=\"\"\n                  src=\"/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-fbfd7.png\"\n                  srcset=\"/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-bf506.png 173w,\n/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-e924d.png 345w,\n/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-fbfd7.png 690w,\n/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-89b1d.png 1035w,\n/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-9c993.png 1380w,\n/d114d5117f6e92da175ac784e5f40b4c-4235e.png 1430w\"\n                  sizes=\"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px\"\n                />\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </a>\n          </div></p>\n<h2 id=\"linking-between-pages\"><a href=\"#linking-between-pages\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Linking between pages</h2>\n<p>Websites are pages and links between pages. While weâ€™ve now got a pretty sweet first pageâ€”one page and no links doesnâ€™t feel very webby. So letâ€™s create a new page.</p>\n<p>First create the link to the new page.</p>\n<p>To do that, import the <code>&#x3C;Link></code> component from the <code>gatsby-link</code> package we installed earlier.</p>\n<p>Unlike the normal HTML <code>&#x3C;a></code> element, our <code>Link</code> component uses <code>to</code> for specifying where youâ€™d like to link to. Letâ€™s link to a page with the pathname of <code>/my-second-gatsby-page/</code>. Try adding that. Once youâ€™re done, the component should look like:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx{2,9-10}\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> Link <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"gatsby-link\"</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">style</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> color<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`tomato`</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello Gatsby<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>What a world<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>http://lorempixel.com/400/200/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>br</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Link</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">to</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>/my-second-gatsby-page/<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Link<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Link</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre>\n<p>Click on that link and again we see the development 404 page.</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s do what it says again and create a new component at <code>src/pages/my-second-gatsby-page.js</code> and save it. Make sure to link back to the home page.</p>\n<p>Now you should be able to click back and forth between the two pages!</p>\n<video controls=\"controls\" autoplay=\"true\" loop=\"true\">\n<source type=\"video/mp4\" src=\"/images/clicking-2.mp4\"></source>\n<p>Your browser does not support the video element.</p>\n</video>\n<h2 id=\"interactive-page\"><a href=\"#interactive-page\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Interactive page</h2>\n<p>One nice thing about using Gatsby for building websites vs other tools is itâ€™s so easy to add interactivity to your pages. React.js was designed for Facebook.com and is used on 1000s of other high-quality web applications.</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s see how easy it is to add interactive elements to our pages.</p>\n<p>Weâ€™ll start by creating a new link to a page at <code>/counter</code>/.</p>\n<p>Add that link to your original <code>index.js</code> page, click on it, and then create a â€œHello Worldâ€ component for <code>/counter/</code> as before. But instead of using whatâ€™s called the â€œfunctional componentâ€ form for React weâ€™ll create a â€œclassâ€ component.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Counter</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Hello Class <span class=\"token class-name\">Component</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Counter</code></pre>\n<p>The class form of React allows us to add component state. Weâ€™ll need that for our counter.</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s continue to flesh out our counter. Letâ€™s add two buttons. One to increment and one to decrement the count of the counter.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx{6-11}\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Counter</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Counter<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>current count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>plus<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>minus<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Counter</code></pre>\n<p>So now we have everything we need to make a nice counter. Letâ€™s make it live.</p>\n<p>First weâ€™ll setup the component state.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx{4-6,12}\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Counter</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">  <span class=\"token function\">constructor</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">    <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span>\n\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Counter<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>current count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>count<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>plus<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>minus<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Counter</code></pre>\n<p>Weâ€™re now rendering the current count from the component state.</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s now change the state when we click on our buttons.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-jsx{14-19}\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Counter</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">React<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Component</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">constructor</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">super</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token function\">render</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Counter<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>h1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>current count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>count<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">onClick</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>count <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">          plus</span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">onClick</span><span class=\"token script language-javascript\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">setState</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> count<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>state<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>count <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">          minus</span>\n<span class=\"highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>button</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></span>\n      <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Counter</code></pre>\n<p>There you go! A working React.js counter inside your static website ğŸ‘Œ</p>\n<p>One fun thing too is that hot reloading isnâ€™t just for content and styles but it works on code as well. Try changing the amount by which clicking on the buttons changes the count.</p>\n<h2 id=\"deploying-gatsbyjs-websites-on-the-web\"><a href=\"#deploying-gatsbyjs-websites-on-the-web\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Deploying Gatsby.js websites on the web</h2>\n<p>Gatsby.js is a <em>static site generator</em> which makes deploying Gatsby sites to\nthe web really easy. There are no servers to setup or complicated databases to\ndeploy.  Instead, the Gatsby <code>build</code> command produces a directory of static\nHTML and JavaScript files which you can deploy to a static site hosting\nservice. (TODO link to deployment docs)</p>\n<p>Letâ€™s try using <a href=\"http://surge.sh/\">Surge</a> for deploying our first Gatsby website.</p>\n<p>First install their terminal tool:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">npm</span> <span class=\"token function\">install</span> --global surge</code></pre>\n<p>Then build your site by running:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">gatsby build</code></pre>\n<p>Building should take 15-30 seconds. Take a look at the generated files by looking\nat the <code>public</code> directory:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">ls</span> public</code></pre>\n<p>Then finally deploy your site by pushing the generated files to surge.sh:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">surge public/</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"good-work\"><a href=\"#good-work\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Good work!</h2>\n<p>In this tutorial, youâ€™ve installed Gatsby, played in the development\nenvironment, and deployed your first site! Awesome! We hope youâ€™re enjoying\nyourself so far. Feel free to continue now on to the second part of the tutorial\nor go exploring around the rest of the site.</p>",
